President Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the opening ceremony of POLIN, the Museum of the History of Polish Jews in Warsaw, Poland. The delegation will be led by Carolyn B. Maloney, a member of the United States House of Representatives. Other members of the delegation include the U.S. Ambassador to Poland, the Special Envoy to Monitor and Combat Anti-Semitism, the Chair of the United States Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad, and representatives from the Department of Treasury and Department of Transportation.